rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E5. Another solar system to explore.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E6. Boat hangar and Boat Parts.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E7. Helicopters.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E8. VTOL Parts for planes.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E9. Customizable parts tabs in SPH and VAB\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E10. Better camera in VAB\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E11. Able to see kerman\u0027s point of\u00A0view on EVA\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gelix","CreatedById":154833,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-17T16:43:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003EI would also\u00A0like it if the science archives would be open in sandbox mode! Instead of storing info on planets in the tracking station, store it in the science archives!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tourist","CreatedById":143403,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-18T01:24:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBase parts! Very needed.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe rest of the list is good too. I don\u0027t really care about boats or helicopters, but others do so, why not.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gelix","CreatedById":154833,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-18T14:50:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222327165\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128043\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450401850\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022143403\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tourist\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Tourist said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBase parts! Very needed.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe rest of the list is good too. I don\u0027t really care about boats or helicopters, but others do so, why not.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m glad you like them!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gelix","CreatedById":154833,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-18T20:36:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also suggest\u00A0some bigger heavy lifting parts!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-20T16:45:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only thing on your list that I think is out of place is\u00A0\u0027another\u00A0solar system\u0027. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you meant\u00A0as a second solar system\u00A0that needs interstellar travel to get there then I can\u0027t see that ever being a standard stock feature as its a bit out of scope.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDifferent or alternative versions of the \u0027single\u0027 system we have would be an interesting thing to have at some point, but again I\u00A0think unlikely to be a stock option for a very long time, if ever. \u00A0Realistically this is an add-on thing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think an expansion of the current solar system by enhancing what\u0027s already there and adding new planets and moons could be a realistic possibility\u00A0with the advent of 64bit in v1.1 though. Though I don\u0027t expect it to happen immediately by any means.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Matt77","CreatedById":69015,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-20T17:48:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222326524\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128043\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450370241\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154833\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gelix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 17/12/2015 at 4:37 PM, Gelix said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E1. Base Parts\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYES.\u00A0 You can build a nice space station or ground base out of rocket parts, but dedicated parts would be excellent.\u00A0 They should be a priority over aircraft parts, which have been getting far too much attention.\u00A0 It\u0027s not Kerbal Flight Program.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222326524\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128043\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450370241\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154833\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gelix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 17/12/2015 at 4:37 PM, Gelix said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E2. A system similar to KIS (Kerbal Inventory System) and KAS\u00A0(Kerbal Attachment\u00A0System)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI haven\u0027t used those mods, but Kerbals do need more reason to EVA than jump out, click \u0022EVA Report\u0022, jump back in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222326524\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128043\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450370241\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154833\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gelix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 17/12/2015 at 4:37 PM, Gelix said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E3. An Observatory (In Career Mode Only) so that you have to find planets and asteroids before they show up in the tracking station.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like that a lot.\u00A0 Mun should be visible from the start, and maybe Minmus.\u00A0 I\u0027d like to see blurry images through the scope and in the tracking station, so you can\u0027t actually see a planet in all it\u0027s glory til you reach it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222326524\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128043\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450370241\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154833\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gelix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 17/12/2015 at 4:37 PM, Gelix said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E11. Able to see kerman\u0027s point of\u00A0view on EVA\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like this idea too, along with better control on spacewalks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs for water / air parts, as I mentioned I think the space parts need more attention first.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gelix","CreatedById":154833,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-20T19:04:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m glad you like my suggestions!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}